This paper discusses the security and searchability of encrypted data, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also introduces novel data structures to improve search efficiency, which is related to database systems (cs.DB). The use of natural language expressions and word-vector space for fuzzy search is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses privacy concerns related to outsourcing data to cloud servers, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a new scheme for search-supported encryption, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
